column30:
The audience_topic_join table needs an additional brand_id included, because the audience-topic relationships are always in the context of some brand.

We will want a migration to add this column, and a seed script that populates the existing rows with the DiGiorno brand id {{d5eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a11}}

We should follow up by adding some logic to the GET /brand/{brandId}/topic endpoint (which gets the audience IDs for each topic) so that when querying the audience_topic_join table for the relationships, it uses both topic_id and brand_id

column182:
AI/Ops endpoint to call: 

You will need to know the host url and have a Databricks token for each respective Databricks workspace/environment.

They’re saved to the respective project/environments in GCP Secrets Manager as 'databricks_host' and 'databricks_token'.



Environment mapping:

prod → clarvos-dbx-prd

staging → clarvos-dbx-stg

dev → ??? (GROOMING: need to figure out what the appropriate databricks environment is for us to rely on in dev)

Ticket for secret access is [https://evolve24.atlassian.net/browse/CLP-1321|https://evolve24.atlassian.net/browse/CLP-1321|smart-link] 



URL: POST ‘{databricks_host}/serving-endpoints/strategy_recommendation_test/invocations’

headers = {

    "Content-Type": "application/json",

    "Authorization": "Bearer {db_auth_token}"

}



Request Body:

{noformat}{
    // These seem necessary
    "strategy_id": "4d129748-537d-481d-b8be-63ffc033e19a",
    "audience_ids": [
        "16b790d4-d54a-4107-b60c-601037efadb3"  // external IDs, not UUIDs! From audience table
    ],
    "topic_ids": [
        "6f4010c6-2fac-43f6-bc90-207d48f495c8" // external IDs, not UUIDs! From topic table
    ],
    "brand_id": "d5eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a11",
    "resonance_score": number // most recent value we have for the brand, from brand_resonance table
    "estimated_total_reach", // The raw number, from the strategy
    // This is optional -- not required for strategy generation, but nice to have if we implement
    "position_statement": string, // From org? Company? Not sure where this would come from if implemented
}{noformat}



In the future, the response will be an async callback to our endpoint defined in [https://evolve24.atlassian.net/browse/CLP-1105|https://evolve24.atlassian.net/browse/CLP-1105|smart-link] . For now, we may be able to capture the response and use it as an input to that endpoint for testing.

